  "description": "The Shirt Tails were a mid-19th-century street gang based in the Five Points slum in Manhattan, New York City. They wore their shirts outside their pants as insignia and concealed weapons beneath. Active from the 1830s to the 1860s, they participated in the New York Draft Riots and disappeared shortly before the American Civil War.",
